body:
This PR is a followup of #7288. Currently marked as draft, since #7288 needs to go first.

Note for review: The change was implemented only by adjusting `find_return_type_of_builtin_method()` and `inferred_method_return_types`

comment_data.body: Based on typeshed here should be `int` not `object`: https://github.com/python/typeshed/blob/cc1c684fe5c8a614808c5d019ade3a876a3a0c95/stdlib/builtins.pyi#L623
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -556,7 +559,7 @@ def _generate_divmod_function(scope, argument_types):
         ljust='T',
         lower='T',
         lstrip='T',
-        maketrans='dict[int,object]',  # staticmethod
+        maketrans='dict[int,int]',  # staticmethod
